cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.PL, cs.RO, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper presents a regression function for planning domains where an agent does not have complete information and may have sensing actions. This is a core problem in AI planning and reasoning. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper presents a planning algorithm that utilizes the regression function. Machine learning techniques are often used in planning algorithms to improve their performance. 
3. cs.PL (Programming Languages) - The paper discusses the use of the 0-approximation to define the regression function. This is a programming language concept that is used to simplify the complexity of the problem. 
4. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper discusses planning domains where an agent may have sensing actions. This is a common problem in robotics, where robots need to sense their environment to plan their actions. 
5. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper presents experimental results with respect to several well-known planning problems in the literature. This is a common practice in software engineering to evaluate the performance of algorithms.
